<plot>A cinematic retelling of William Shakespeare's classic farce, The Shrew in the Park follows a community theatre group staging "The Taming of the Shrew" as a Shakespeare in the Park production. We see the backstage drama, the long hours of preparation, the crappy jobs, as the actors make sacrifices to do what they love best: get up on stage and perform. The entire text of the play is the movie's only dialogue.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?590608</url></doc>
